Cooling

Started at 14:54 pm.
- Brain temperature was 35.5 deg, warmed up to 37 deg.
Cooled down to 34 deg at 08:45 am (next day).

Cooling set up

1st target = -15 deg (VT output air)
Flow rate = 60 SLPM
2nd target = 37 deg (brain temp to cool down to)
Maintenance time = 960 min once brain reached 33 deg
3rd target temperature = 38 deg (rewarm target)
Rewarm rate = 0.25 deg/h

Description

For the first 2-h the brain temperature gradually increased from 35.5oC immediately after FPI to 37oC which was set as the maintenance temperature. Starting from 8 h post FPI, the ICP and Heart rate started to increase and has to be controlled by max PPF, FNL and 0.5% ISO. The CTP at 11.5 hour post (2:15 am) showed massive decrease in blood flow to the cortex. After reviewing the results, at 8:45 am decided to cool down the brain to 34oC. As soon as the brain temperature dropped, the ICP and heart rate drops in synchrony. Decided to decrease the Iso to 0% from 0.25% then ICP and heart rate increased, turned back ISO to 0.25% to stabilize the ICP and heart rate.
